# Environment files
# See knowledge-base/README.md#environment-variable-management-pattern

# Local secrets and overrides (never committed)
.envrc.local

# .env* — kept ignored as a safety net, NOT part of this pattern.
# direnv/devenv does NOT load these: the committed .envrc sources .envrc.local,
# never .env. They stay ignored only so a framework that reads .env natively
# (Next.js, Vite, docker-compose) can't leak secrets. For direnv-loaded secrets,
# use .envrc.local instead.
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local

# Committed files (do NOT gitignore):
# .envrc              — direnv/devenv boilerplate, no secrets
# .envrc.local.example — documents required secrets for the project
